      "text": "Acute severe exacerbation triggered by viral URI in patient with known moderate persistent asthma on dual-controller therapy. Presented with SpO2 89% on room air, tachypnea to 38, intercostal and subcostal retractions. Resolved with continuous albuterol nebulization, ipratropium, and IV methylprednisolone over 4-hour observation period."
